Hypothesis testing - type I and type II errors

Brandon Parmanand

july, 30 2022

Assignment:Perform hypothesis testing with this data and these hypotheses. Draw the distribution and rejection region by hand. Complete the hypothesis test manually, then use the function in R.

2.5 1.9 3.0 -0.1 1.6 3.1 1.4 1.6 0.7 0.4

* Ho: \(\mu \le 0\)

* Ha: \(\mu > 0\)

x <- c(2.5, 1.9, 3.0, -0.1, 1.6, 3.1, 1.4, 1.6, 0.7, 0.4)

risk_tolerance <- 0.05
mean_sample <- mean(x)
sd_sample <- sd(x)
n <- length(x)

(mean_sample - 0)/(sd_sample/sqrt(n))
## [1] 4.761684
cutoff <- qt(
  p = risk_tolerance,
  df = n - 1,
  lower.tail = FALSE
)
cutoff
## [1] 1.833113
t.test(
  x = x,
  alternative = "greater",
  mu = 0,
  conf.level = 0.95
)
## 
##  One Sample t-test
## 
## data:  x
## t = 4.7617, df = 9, p-value = 0.0005136
## alternative hypothesis: true mean is greater than 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.9901957       Inf
## sample estimates:
## mean of x 
##      1.61

Reject Ho in favor Ha

_______________________________________________________

* Ho: \(\mu \ge 0\)

* Ha: \(\mu < 0\)

-0.1 0.0 -0.6 -0.9 1.8 1.7 -0.2 2.0 1.2 2.0

x <- c(0.1,0.0,-0.6,-0.9,1.8,1.7,-0.2,2.0,1.2,2.0)

risk_tolerance <- 0.05
mean_sample <- mean(x)
sd_sample <- sd(x)
n <- length(x)

(mean_sample - 0)/(sd_sample/sqrt(n))
## [1] 1.965075
cutoff <- qt(
  p = risk_tolerance,
  df = n - 1, 
  lower.tail = TRUE
)
cutoff
## [1] -1.833113
t.test(
  x = x,
  alternative = "less",
  mu = 0,
  conf.level = 0.95
)
## 
##  One Sample t-test
## 
## data:  x
## t = 1.9651, df = 9, p-value = 0.9595
## alternative hypothesis: true mean is less than 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##      -Inf 1.372321
## sample estimates:
## mean of x 
##      0.71

Fail to reject the null hypothesis.

_______________________________________________________

* Ho: \(\mu = 0\)

* Ha: \(\mu \ne 0\)

-0.7 -0.3 1.8 2.2 2.3 0.4 -0.2 1.8 1.9 1.

x <- c(-0.7,-0.3,1.8,2.2,2.3,0.4,-0.2,1.8,1.9,1)

risk_tolerance <- 0.05
mean_sample <- mean(x)
sd_sample <- sd(x)
n <- length(x)

(mean_sample - 0)/(sd_sample/sqrt(n))
## [1] 2.841629
cutoff_left <- qt(
  p = 0.05/2,
  df = n - 1,
  lower.tail = TRUE
)
cutoff_left
## [1] -2.262157
cutoff_right <- qt(
  p = 0.05/2,
  df = n - 1,
  lower.tail = FALSE
)
cutoff_right
## [1] 2.262157
t.test(
  x = x,
  alternative = "two.sided",
  mu = 0,
  conf.level = 0.95
)
## 
##  One Sample t-test
## 
## data:  x
## t = 2.8416, df = 9, p-value = 0.01935
## alternative hypothesis: true mean is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.2080008 1.8319992
## sample estimates:
## mean of x 
##      1.02

Reject Ho in favor Ha
